Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Meanwhile, trim the @butternut squash{1}(trimmed), halve lengthways, then scoop out the
seeds (peel first if you prefer). Cut into 2cm chunks.

Pop the diced butternut onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, sprinkle over
half the @curry powder mix{1/2%sachet} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat.
Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, pour the @water{300%ml} into a medium #saucepan{} with a tight-fitting
lid. Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil.
Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and
leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will
continue to cook in its own steam).

While everything cooks, halve any thick @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g}(halved lengthways),
then cut them into thirds.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the
@korma curry paste{50%g}, garlic and remaining @curry powder mix{1/2%sachet}, stir-fry
for ~{1%minute}, then stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @water{100%ml}.

Stir in the broccoli and bring to the boil. Once boiling, lower the heat, cover
with a #lid{} and simmer until the broccoli is just tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Next, stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @mango chutney{40%g}. Bring back to the
boil, then remove from the heat. Season with salt and pepper.

Once the butternut squash is roasted, stir it through the curry. Return the pan to
the heat to warm through. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Fluff up the rice with a fork and share between your plates, then top with your
korma style curry. Top with the @diced British chicken breast{260%g}(diced).

Enjoy!